Name: AXLE CENTRE DISTANCE OF HEAVIEST VEHICLE IN CENTIMETRES
Explanation: DISTANCE FROM THE CENTRE OF AN AXLE (OF A VEHICLE) TO THE CENTRE OF A NEIGHBOURING AXLE MEASURED IN CENTIMETRES. A HYPHEN "-" INDICATES A NO DATA MARKER FOR THE LAST AXEL DISTANCE AS THERE IS NO DISTANCE TO THE NEXT AXLE TO REPORT.
